Blu","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"An emotive singer and poetic song-writer, Edy Blu’s unique blend of psychadelic soul, hip-pop, and jazz leaves one feeling every word she sings. She has a knack for writing and composing catchy, melody-driven songs that are easy to relate and dance to. Reminiscent of Sade, Adele, and Erykah Badu, Edy Blu is still an authentic creation. 

A Virginia native, Edy was born and raised on a farm in the Shenandoah Valley. A natural dreamer, the back-drop of mountains and woods only fueled Edy’s free-spirited tendencies. Yearning for more worldly experiences, Ms. Blu relocated to Sydney, Australia. It was during her three years abroad that she began to realize her musical potential by performing at various showcases and open mics. 

As music became more than just a hobby, she crossed the Pacific and found herself in Washington, D.C. She became the lead singer of a rock and roll band to hone her voice and stage presence. She was also given the opportunity to sit in with reggae powerhouse, See-I at Eighteenth Street Lounge on Wednesday nights. These experiences gave her the confidence to start her own band in 2012. 

Her soulful, rootsy vibe and energizing live performances have been garnering her fans around the DMV. In 2013, Edy performed around the country, including at the Napa Film Festival while supporting the release of a film called The Hornets Nest. She is featured on the upcoming See-I album, ‘Knowledge Shine Bright’, set to be released in May 2014. Currently, Edy Blu is working on her own recording project, which will be available later this
